3(5-4p) = 13p
p = \frac{15}{25} = \frac{3}{5}
\begin{align*} \Pr[L] &= \Pr[L \mid H]\Pr[H] + \Pr[L \mid \bar H]\Pr[\bar H] \\ &= \frac{p}{20} + \frac{1-p}{4} \\ &= \frac{5-4p}{20}. \end{align*}
\Pr[H \mid L]\Pr[L] = \Pr[L \cap H] = \Pr[L \mid H]\Pr[H],
\frac{3}{13}\left(\frac{5-4p}{20}\right) = \frac{p}{20}.
